18/12/2002
TIRANA, Albania -- Artur Zheji, director general of Albanian Public Radio and Television, officially apologised Tuesday (17 December) for the broadcast of a sketch depicting Pope John Paul II. The apology was presented to parliament's Media and Public Information Committee. The sketch was severely criticised by the Vatican Embassy in Tirana, which sought a formal apology. (Albanian News - 18/12/02; ATA - 17/12/02)
